  emsenn:Sources "Wille, R. 'Restructuring Lattice Theory: An Approach Based on Hierarchies of Concepts.' Ordered Sets, 1982." , "Ganter, B. and Wille, R. Formal Concept Analysis: Mathematical Foundations. Springer, 1999." , "Ginsberg, M. 'Multivalued Logics: A Uniform Approach to Reasoning in AI.' Computational Intelligence, 1988." , "Fitting, M. 'Bilattices and the Semantics of Logic Programming.' Journal of Logic Programming, 1991." , "Belnap, N. 'A Useful Four-Valued Logic.' Modern Uses of Multiple-Valued Logic, 1977." , "Angluin, D. 'Inductive Inference of Formal Languages from Positive Data.' Information and Control, 1980." , "Gold, E. M. 'Language Identification in the Limit.' Information and Control, 1967." , "Davey, B. and Priestley, H. Introduction to Lattices and Order. Cambridge University Press, 2002." , "Bloom, B. 'Learning for Mastery.' Evaluation Comment, 1968." , "Lave, J. and Wenger, E. Situated Learning: Legitimate Peripheral Participation. Cambridge University Press, 1991." , "Carlsson, G. 'Topology and Data.' Bulletin of the AMS, 2009." , "Kaburlasos, V. G. Towards a Unified Modeling and Knowledge-Representation Based on Lattice Theory. Springer, 2006." , "Liquière, M. and Sallantin, J. 'Structural Machine Learning with Galois Lattice and Graphs.' ICML, 1998." , "Clark, A. 'Learning Context Free Grammars with the Syntactic Concept Lattice.' ICGI, 2010." , "Jipsen, P. and Tsinakis, C. 'A Survey of Residuated Lattices.' Ordered Algebraic Structures, 2002." ;
